JOHANNESBURG - The Methodist church in Meadowlands, Soweto held a memorial service for the late struggle icon Winnie Madikizela-Mandela on Sunday afternoon. On Sunday morning, the church's main service was dedicated to her. We are still in Meadowlands. Memorial Service of South African leader #WinnieMadikizelaMandela - watch @eNCA from 14:00 pic.twitter.com/u7Pin8FvF3 "Mama Winnie", as she is affectionately known, attended a five-hour service at the church just days before her death on 2 April. eNCA